# Project conventions
- Before changing code, read and follow AGENTS.md — the single source of truth for this repo's conventions and reliability guardrails (shared with Claude Code and Codex).
- CRITICAL: any code that touches the database and also does I/O must follow the "Database Session Discipline" section of AGENTS.md (short transactions; never hold a DB session across RouterOS/payment/HTTP I/O; telemetry commits in its own session). It is the #1 cause of production outages here.

You are in CONCISE MODE.
- Output = code or diff only, unless I explicitly write "explain".
- Explanations, if asked, must be under 80 words.
- Never generate README/tutorial/boilerplate comments unprompted.
- If unsure, ask 1 short clarifying question instead of speculating.
